# Shadcn/ui Guidelines

## Why Shadcn/ui?
- Components are COPIED into your repo (not installed as a library)
- AI agents can READ and MODIFY the component code directly
- No need to consult external documentation

## Component Location
- All Shadcn components live in `components/ui/`
- Custom components live in `components/`
- Never modify `components/ui/` files directly — customize via props or wrapper components

## Styling with cn()
Always use the `cn()` utility for conditional classes:
```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

<div className={cn(
  "base-classes",
  isActive && "active-classes",
  variant === "destructive" && "text-destructive"
)} />
```

## Common Components

### Button
Use variants: default, destructive, outline, secondary, ghost, link
```tsx
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';

<Button variant="default">Primary</Button>
<Button variant="destructive">Delete</Button>
<Button variant="outline">Cancel</Button>
<Button variant="ghost">Subtle</Button>
```

### Card
```tsx
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardDescription, CardContent, CardFooter } from '@/components/ui/card';

<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
    <CardDescription>Description</CardDescription>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>Content here</CardContent>
  <CardFooter>Footer actions</CardFooter>
</Card>
```

### Table
```tsx
import { Table, TableHeader, TableBody, TableRow, TableHead, TableCell } from '@/components/ui/table';

<Table>
  <TableHeader>
    <TableRow>
      <TableHead>Column</TableHead>
    </TableRow>
  </TableHeader>
  <TableBody>
    <TableRow>
      <TableCell>Data</TableCell>
    </TableRow>
  </TableBody>
</Table>
```

### Form Inputs
```tsx
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';
import { Label } from '@/components/ui/label';
import { Select, SelectContent, SelectItem, SelectTrigger, SelectValue } from '@/components/ui/select';

<div className="space-y-2">
  <Label htmlFor="name">Name</Label>
  <Input id="name" placeholder="Enter name" />
</div>
```

### Dialog (Modal)
```tsx
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogHeader, DialogTitle, DialogTrigger } from '@/components/ui/dialog';

<Dialog>
  <DialogTrigger asChild>
    <Button>Open</Button>
  </DialogTrigger>
  <DialogContent>
    <DialogHeader>
      <DialogTitle>Modal Title</DialogTitle>
    </DialogHeader>
    {/* Content */}
  </DialogContent>
</Dialog>
```

### Toast Notifications
```tsx
import { useToast } from '@/components/ui/use-toast';

const { toast } = useToast();

toast({
  title: "Success",
  description: "Operation completed",
});
```

## Icons
Always use Lucide React:
```tsx
import { Loader2, Check, X, ChevronRight, Plus, Trash2, Edit, Search } from 'lucide-react';

// Loading spinner
<Loader2 className="h-4 w-4 animate-spin" />

// In buttons
<Button>
  <Plus className="h-4 w-4 mr-2" />
  Add Item
</Button>
```

## Loading States
Use Loader2 with animate-spin for consistent loading indicators:
```tsx
if (isLoading) {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center justify-center p-8">
      <Loader2 className="h-6 w-6 animate-spin" />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Responsive Patterns
Use Tailwind breakpoints with Shadcn components:
```tsx
<Card className="w-full md:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3">
  {/* Responsive card */}
</Card>
```
